The paper presents a general model for probabilistic calculations and applies it to various problems in computational biology. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IT (information theory), and cs.BIO (bioinformatics). However, given the focus on automata and pattern matching, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG and cs.IT for their relevance to probabilistic modeling and analysis. Finally, cs.BIO is also a possible sub-category given the specific applications discussed in the paper.
